b?topicID=716.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Easy way to learn chain casting of pets...</span><hr size=1> I'm level 57, and we have a level 52 Mage in our guild.  We've both done some chaincasting, but not much, and not enough to feel safe in a serious solo spot.<br>
<br>
So I asked her if she wanted to help us learn how to chaincast effeciantly.  We found a nice spot in Skyfire to pull to and we did <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> group up.  Rather we soloed next to each other chaincasting.  If one of us got in trouble the other would bail them out.  We strictly tried to go with the pets doing most of the damage using our low level spells to &quot;tag&quot; the mob for exp.<br>
<br>
It didn't last long as fellow guild mates showed up to group, but while it did last it worked well at safely getting some practice in.<br>
<br>
Might want to give it a try if you're not well versed in chaincasting. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
p.s. when our guild leader showed up, a level 57 Cleric, the three of us pretty much owned anything pulled our way, nice combo, two Mages and a Complete Healing Cleric. <p>Ansi Firetosser <BR> 50-ish Mage on Tunare <BR>  Proud member of the Echoes Guild<br><br><br>
<img src="http://crodley.home.mindspring.com/watch.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukinelaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kinelaria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 342<br> <font color=#333333>(9/20/02 1:49:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=716.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Easy way to learn chain casting of pets...</span><hr size=1> I found chain casting to be pretty easy, though I dreaded trying it for a long time. It's alot like timing heals as a cleric or other healer (though it is more like timing a complete heal than any of the smaller heals).<br>
<br>
Just gotta watch how fast your pet is losing health. A bit before the pet is likely to die during the casting of your next pet, you begin casting the next pet (leave yourself room at first, and adjust from there). When the casting bubble gets to around half a purple left, dismiss your current pet if it's still alive. Don't try any lower than half a casting bubble, I've found this usually doesn't give enough time to dismiss the pet and you wind up with the &quot;can't have more than one pet&quot; message. Course your results will likely vary.<br>
<br>
Only drawback to this method is you burn through malachite like nothing else. But the results are worthwhile and malachite is cheap =).<br>
<br>
