 </a><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uithryn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ithryn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 103<br> <font color=#333333>(9/20/02 3:44:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=716.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re</span><hr size=1> Actually, the easy way to learn to chaincast pets is to go to EC and kill spiders or bears with your lvl 8 pet.<br>
<br>
Why learn a new skill by casting spells that cost 300-400 mana against mobs that can kill you if you screw up?<br>
<br>
If you screw up in EC, the worst that will happen is you'll get hit for 5 points of damage every 20 seconds or so...<br>
<br>
Heck, you can even stand in Freeport and load up your 4th level pets and just practice your timing on the casting and /pet get lost commands.<br>
<br>
I don't like making things harder and more dangerous than they need to be <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utipareth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tipareth</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.bota.org/images/cubota2o.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#333333>(9/20/02 5:14:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=716.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://popii.tripod.co.jp/gandalf2_icon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Re</span><hr size=1> A good safe way to learn chain casting?  Either 1) sow potions or 2) Jboots <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :x --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/sick.gif ALT=":x"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="350">
