<br>
However, be aware that there is a bug with the new UI.  About once or twice a day, it seems, the UI breaks so that no matter active part of the screen I click onto, the only effect is that the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> PET INFO =&gt; GO AWAY</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> button <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>appears</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> as if it is being depressed, but nothing happens.  That is, if I try to use the cursor to cast a spell, press a button or hotkey, remove a buff, access inventory, right-click an item, use a menu, or click onto a window so that it gains focus, nothing happens except the PET GO AWAY button looks like it is being pressed.  Only the command line works at this point.  Camping out and back in restores the UI.<br>
<br>
I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /bug</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> this every time it occurs, but not surprisingly, there is no response or any evidence that the contents of the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /bug</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> report window are not flushed when the window is closed.  In desperation, I wrote <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Absor</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, whose reply was succinct: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;We are aware of these bugs, they will be fixed eventually, but not any time soon.&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
