<br>
Nah!  Like I said earlier and CelanXev reiterated, if you're just wanting to learn the skill, take 15 minutes and go to kill some lvl 10 mobs or so.<br>
<br>
Use a pet that can't solo them, like a lvl 8 pet.<br>
<br>
That way, you can try dozens of times without running out of mana and if you screw it up, you can laugh hysterically as the mob beats on you.  You can even run, yelling for help, through a newbie camp and then give them all lava shields for helping you out.<br>
<br>
You'll get it down in 10 minutes easy and you won't have to worry about dying. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uithryn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ithryn</A> at: 9/20/02 7:26:47 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukrilenspiritlink.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krilen Spiritlink</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 354<br> <font color=#333333>(9/20/02 7:35:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=716.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> Just remember, don't use any high agro spells like SoFB or anything until you're sure it's your last pet in the chain. Otherwise you have to wait for root to land, taunt to work, or the pet to do near the same amount of dmg while you run around &gt;&lt;<br>
<br>
Oh, and when you find a new mob, test different pets. I remember, bax pre-epic and stuff in the grey, I would use 51 earth, because mobs were easy enough that I could spend the extra 100 mana and never have the mana bar go down. However, with 57 earth, I'd kill faster, but start to get in debt to the mana pool.<br>
<br>
So, the morale is... Losing mana while chain casting defeats the whole purpose. The purpose of chain casting is that it allows any mage to solo very effectively and leisurely with no down time, not even to cannipet or anything. Chain casting pets, if done correctly and in the correct environment, is quite peaceful and refreshing, even if it's not always better than chain nuking and cannipetting.<br>
<br>
 <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=109465>~Krilen</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/useek9.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seek 9</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 594<br> <font color=#333333>(9/20/02 8:51:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=716.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> For really tough mobs that are at the limit of your ability to solo, even with pet chain casting, you can do a lot of prep work to make it sucessful.   (An example is killing Slixin Klex at Mage levels 50 to 53 - a close fight).<br>
<br>
What I do is summon a pet and deck it out in full armor, all the summoned focus, lev rings (more ac).   I will drop a couple mod rods on the ground and have one in inventory.   Burnout and flame shield that first pet, nearly med to full, then /pet attack and finish medding.<br>
<br>
You will note that that first pet will go down a lot slower and do more damage then the rest.   The remaining pets should be very cheap.  For me, this means a shovel-focused 49 earth pet (200 mana, thats it), never burnout, just a lava shield.   Med as much as possible between summons.<br>
<br>
Consume mod rods as you go along, regening your health via prebuffed Phantom armor.<br>
<br>
Even non-uber Mages like me can do quite well with such techniques. <p><u>Seek Pyremaker</u><br>
Mage 55th Season, Xegony<br>
The Ring of Truth
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uchardandhispet.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chard and his pet</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#333333>(9/25/02 12:26:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=716.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Easy way to learn chain casting of pets...</span><hr size=1> This might seem a bit obvious but no one's mentioned it yet.  When chain casting, make sure you have a good link connection with no lag.  I've been lagged a few times when I've been trying to do the critical timing on /pet get lost, not very pleasant.<br>
<br>
Apart from that I can say that Seafury Cyclopses were made for chain casting, you can finish off a kill with a fresh pet on full health and you with virtually no net mana loss.<br>
<br>
To really tune in the skill with multiple chains on a 10000+ HP mob, Slixin Klex is an ideal practice target, and you should get your epic drop as reward. <p>Chard  57 Conjurer of Campaigni Callidus<BR>Bertoxxulous</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showPrevMessage?topicID=716.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showNextMessage?topicID=716.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=716.topic&index=16><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.threadControl?topicID=716.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=716.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=716.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements">Administration<option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option value="themagicianstowerfrm32">Class Balance<option value="themagicianstowerfrm45">User Interface<option value="themagicianstowerspells">Spells<option valu